[2] UK (South Wales)
Date: Tue 19 Mar 2013
Source: This is South Wales [edited]
http://www.thisissouthwales.co.uk/Measles-outbreak-alert-parents/story-18460019-detail/story.html#axzz2O5mZPsDt


Schools in Neath, Port Talbot, and Carmarthenshire have so far not been affected by the measles outbreak, but parents there are also being advised to heed Public Health Wales's advice to get vaccinated.

Advice from public health Wales has been sent to every school in the Neath Port Talbot county, urging parents to have their children vaccinated as quickly as possible and to remain vigilant for symptoms, which include red/brown spots, watery eyes and sneezing. And parents in Carmarthenshire are also being advised to remain alert. "I'd urge all parents in Carmarthenshire to please get their children vaccinated. "This outbreak is becoming very concerning, and the cases are not too far away from us in the Swansea Valley."

