[3] UK (South Wales)
Date: Thu 21 Mar 2013
Source: ITV Wales [edited]
http://www.itv.com/news/wales/update/2013-03-20/number-of-measles-cases-reaches-316/


Public Health Wales is urging parents to get their children vaccinated, as the number of measles cases reaches 316.

According to new figures, there have been 64 new cases reported in the past week. The disease has now spread to children in 111 secondary and primary schools, nurseries and playgroups. The majority of cases are in the Swansea area, but cases are increasingly being reported across the Mid and West Wales region.

