[6] Pakistan (Sindh)
Date: Wed 20 Mar 2013
Source: Central Asia Online [edited]
http://centralasiaonline.com/en_GB/articles/caii/newsbriefs/2013/03/20/newsbrief-04


An on-going measles outbreak in Sindh province has killed 20 people so far in March [2013], with more than 300 children afflicted, the provincial health department said on Tue 19 Mar 2013.

Ten deaths were reported in Tharparkar, 4 in Tando Muhammad Khan, 3 in Hyderabad, and 2 in Badin, SAMAA reported, citing health officials. A location for the 20th death was not specified.

Measles has killed hundreds of children in Pakistan this year [2013].

--
